---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy" description="How Leonida Ledger handles official GTA 6 sources, rumors, corrections, copyright, and independent coverage.">
  <header class="page-header shell">
    <div class="page-kicker">Editorial policy</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">Editorial Policy</h1>
    <p class="page-intro">
      We publish concise GTA 6 answers from official sources, correct mistakes, and keep rumors out of factual guidance.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="section-tight shell split">
    <div class="panel">
      <h2>How We Report GTA 6</h2>
      <p>Rockstar Games, Take-Two, PlayStation, Xbox, and official store pages are our primary sources.</p>
      <p>Details visible only in trailers or screenshots are described as observations. Rumors and anonymous leaks are not presented as facts.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="panel">
      <h2>Corrections And Rights</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Send the page URL, the detail that is wrong, and a supporting official link.</li>
        <li>Rights requests should identify the relevant image or page and the rights holder.</li>
        <li>We update material facts when an official source changes.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><a href="/sources/">View GTA 6 sources and correction details.</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

